                            <comment id="16841478" author="hachikuji" created="Thu, 16 May 2019 15:43:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This could be caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8275&quot; title=&quot;NetworkClient leastLoadedNode selection should consider throttled nodes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8275&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8275&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I will have a patch ready soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16841496" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 16 May 2019 16:00:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hachikuji commented on pull request #6746: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8376&quot; title=&quot;Flaky test ClientAuthenticationFailureTest.testTransactionalProducerWithInvalidCredentials test.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8376&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8376&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; Least loaded node should consider connections which are being prepared&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/6746&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/6746&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   This fixes a regression caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8275&quot; title=&quot;NetworkClient leastLoadedNode selection should consider throttled nodes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8275&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8275&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The least loaded node selection should take into account nodes which are currently being connect to. This includes both the CONNECTING and CHECKING_API_VERSIONS states since `canSendRequest` would return false in either case.&lt;/p&gt;

